note: Title from title page (f. 1r); other title from beginning of work (f. 1v).
Three owner's notes, two of which are dated 1212 A.H. (1797 CE) and 1246 A.H. (1830 CE) (second front flyleaf recto) and two effaced stamps (first and second front flyleaves recto).

msContents.summary: Copy of a work on horoscopes. A short introduction precedes numerous tables of their risings and settings.

supportDesc.extent: 77 foliated leaves : 220 x 136 (130 x 83) mm, bound to 220 x 142 x 13 mm

layoutDesc.layout: Written in 23 long lines or in 10-column tables; border-ruled.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in nastaʻlīq in black ink; pointed.

origin.p: The item is undated; possibly produced in the 18th century.

provenance: Formerly owned by al-Sayyid al-Ḥājj Ismāʻīl ibn Pīr Muḥammad Afandī Sarūrī (note in ink second front flyleaf recto).
Formerly owned by [...] Dahīʹzādah, 1212 A.H. (1797 CE) (note in ink second front flyleaf recto).
Formerly owned by Ibrāhīmʹzādah Ismāʻīl Z̲ihnī?, 1246 A.H. (1830 CE) (note in ink second front flyleaf recto).
Formerly owned by George Arthur Plimpton (bookplates inside front and back covers).
